TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Sql Query
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: with bca (clm_gid, btch_gid, payr_id, risk_cd) as (select bca.CLM_GID, bca.BTCH_GID, bca.PAYR_ID, bca.RISK_CD from vrap.RCIT_BASE_CLM_apc bca where bca.PAYR_ID between 28200 and 28299 and bca.RISK_CD is null and BTCH_DT >= '2014-01-01') select bca.CLM_GID, bca.BTCH_GID, bca.PAYR_ID, bca.RISK_CD, inv.ALGN_LVL_GID, inv.inv_elig_dt from bca join vrap.rcit_base_clm_inv inv on inv.CLM_GID = bca.CLM_GID and inv.BTCH_GID = bca.BTCH_GID where inv.INV_ELIG_DT between $$MAX_QTR_STRT_DT and $$MAX_QTR_END_DT and inv.MODEL_TYP_CD = 'T' with ur

SESSION.DESCRIPTION: This session can be used to get date ranges for certain period types. It uses the VRAP.VRCIT_MODEL_PRD_STUS view, and you pass in the CLM_LOCK_CD and APC_STAT_CD values. It puts out the MIN/MAX Quarter period and Monthly periods, along with their associated Start and End dates, based on what values you pass in. Since it builds a Parameter file for use in another session, you also need to pass in the Folder, Workflow, and the Worklet or Session that will be using the new Parameter file.
